Obs.: In May 9, Pouso Alegre, a team from 2nd Level not promoted in
1988 (Democrata-GV was the runner-up), wins in the sports court the right to play the 1st
Level of 1989. The reason was the annulment and replay of a match against Atlético de Três Corações,
who walked over the rescheduled match.

Pouso Alegre’s matches, played at the same time of the Final Phase, were:

[May 11] Esportivo     7-1  Pouso Alegre
[May 14] Democrata-SL  1-0  Pouso Alegre
[May 16] Pouso Alegre  2-2  Uberaba
[May 18] Pouso Alegre  1-0  Fabril
[May 21] Rio Branco    0-0  Pouso Alegre
[May 24] Pouso Alegre  0-2  Cruzeiro
[May 26] Democrata-GV  1-0  Pouso Alegre
[May 28] América       5-2  Pouso Alegre
[May 30] Pouso Alegre  0-1  Flamengo
[Jun 01] Atlético      1-1  Pouso Alegre
[Jun 04] Tupi          1-0  Pouso Alegre
[Jun 11] Pouso Alegre  3-0  Caldense
[Jun 15] Pouso Alegre  2-0  Villa Nova
[Jun 25] Pouso Alegre  1-0  Valeriodoce
[Jul 02] Pouso Alegre  1-0  Nacional
[Jul 16] Uberlândia    4-0  Pouso Alegre

América, placed fourth in group A, had to wait the matches of Pouso Alegre –
if Pouso Alegre trespassed América, the latter would be eliminated. Due to this,
América entered later the Final Phase.

